{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, Ayaz et al. (2019b) found that smart irrigation systems utilizing IoT sensors can reduce water usage by up to 30% while maintaining or even improving crop yields.",
    "IoT technology plays a crucial role in minimizing agricultural waste by ensuring timely harvest and optimal storage conditions through IoT-driven supply chain management systems.",
    "This, in turn, reduces post-harvest losses.",
    "A study by Wolfert et al. (2017) found that implementing IoT systems in the agricultural supply chain resulted in up to a 15% reduction in overall food waste by improving logistics and storage management.",
    "The Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) also reported a 40% decrease in post-harvest food waste due to the implementation of IoT in supply chain management."
  ]
}